From now on, you can start your dream life.

492
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,759
If you're unhappy living in the villa...

493
00:26:17,759 --> 00:26:19,480
or if you feel lonely,

494
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:21,440
you can take your family with you.

495
00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:23,160
You can let them move in too.

496
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,279
Then all of you can live happily.

497
00:26:26,160 --> 00:26:27,240
Won't that be great?

498
00:26:28,519 --> 00:26:30,119
You can even take them out.

499
00:26:30,319 --> 00:26:31,720
You can go anywhere.

500
00:26:32,079 --> 00:26:34,160
You can show them around the world.

501
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,559
You can go to the US, Europe,

502
00:26:35,559 --> 00:26:36,680
or anywhere you like.

503
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:40,440
I'm happy as long as you're happy.

504
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,839
Okay?

505
00:26:47,960 --> 00:26:49,200
I'll think about it.

506
00:26:54,039 --> 00:26:55,480
Will you stop thinking?

507
00:26:55,960 --> 00:26:58,279
My heart turned cold when you said you would think about it.

508
00:27:19,839 --> 00:27:20,839
What's wrong?

509
00:27:20,839 --> 00:27:22,000
Monkey, I'm in trouble.

510
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:23,359
My car fell into the river. It won't turn on.

511
00:27:23,359 --> 00:27:24,599
Come and save me. Hurry.

512
00:27:25,599 --> 00:27:27,759
In that case, you should call for help.

513
00:27:27,759 --> 00:27:30,279
- Why are you looking for me? - Are you going to pay for it?

514
00:27:30,279 --> 00:27:31,599
Besides, the car would have sank by the time they reach.

515
00:27:31,599 --> 00:27:32,720
Hurry up. Come on.

516
00:27:32,720 --> 00:27:34,119
I'm busy.

517
00:27:34,119 --> 00:27:36,079
Busy with what? Come and help me. Come on.

518
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:37,519
Hurry up.

519
00:27:37,519 --> 00:27:38,559
Beg me nicely.

520
00:27:38,759 --> 00:27:40,799
I'm sorry. I'm begging you, buddy.

521
00:27:40,799 --> 00:27:41,880
I'm begging you. Please come quickly.

522
00:27:41,880 --> 00:27:42,960
Just wait there.

523
00:27:52,279 --> 00:27:53,519
It's raining.

524
00:27:57,920 --> 00:27:58,920
Hello?

525
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:03,000
Where are you?

526
00:28:03,119 --> 00:28:05,480
We're almost there. Don't rush me.

527
00:28:05,640 --> 00:28:06,680
We're on our way.

528
00:28:07,279 --> 00:28:08,680
Hold on. We're almost there.

529
00:28:09,720 --> 00:28:10,920
I didn't notice when I called earlier.

530
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:12,279
My car has slipped into the water.

531
00:28:12,559 --> 00:28:13,680
If you don't come out now,

532
00:28:13,680 --> 00:28:15,240
it will disappear into thin air and never be seen again.

533
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:16,319
All right, that's enough.

534
00:28:16,319 --> 00:28:17,559
Save the battery.

535
00:28:17,559 --> 00:28:19,400
I won't be able to reach you if your phone is dead.

536
00:28:19,599 --> 00:28:22,759
Can you try to be as efficient as when you're saving others?

537
00:28:22,759 --> 00:28:25,079
Or else, you'll never see me again. Hurry up!

538
00:28:25,079 --> 00:28:26,079
All right, I understand.

539
00:28:26,079 --> 00:28:27,119
I'm hanging up.

540
00:28:37,559 --> 00:28:39,200
If it weren't for Hai Xing,

541
00:28:39,319 --> 00:28:41,839
we wouldn't have had the chance...

542
00:28:42,079 --> 00:28:43,759
to travel in the storm.

543
00:28:44,079 --> 00:28:46,240
It feels quite romantic, doesn't it?

544
00:28:47,319 --> 00:28:48,400
It's too bad that it's raining heavily.

545
00:29:35,319 --> 00:29:38,519
I'm fine. Hurry and help me get my car out.

546
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:40,799
I'll take care of it tomorrow. Get in the car first.

547
00:29:40,799 --> 00:29:42,079
No way. It will turn into a total loss by tomorrow.

548
00:29:42,079 --> 00:29:43,119
We've been together for 10 years.

549
00:29:43,119 --> 00:29:44,599
Your engine is completely submerged. It's beyond salvage.

550
00:29:44,599 --> 00:29:45,599
No way! I'm with my car no matter what.

551
00:29:45,599 --> 00:29:46,839
Help, Monkey!

552
00:29:52,799 --> 00:29:54,279
What are you doing? Help me!

553
00:29:59,720 --> 00:30:00,799
What are you doing?

554
00:30:00,799 --> 00:30:02,759
Give me a hand. Don't just stand there, okay?

555
00:30:14,720 --> 00:30:16,559
Hou Jue.

556
00:30:16,920 --> 00:30:18,000
Take it.

557
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,039
Control it and I'll drive.

558
00:30:21,079 --> 00:30:22,799
Get the rope. Don't just stand there!

559
00:30:29,359 --> 00:30:30,559
Help me out!

560
00:30:30,799 --> 00:30:31,799
Help!

561
00:30:45,279 --> 00:30:46,480
Go!

562
00:30:46,680 --> 00:30:47,720
Go!

563
00:30:50,319 --> 00:30:51,319
Activate the winch!

564
00:30:51,559 --> 00:30:52,680
Activate the winch!

565
00:30:58,720 --> 00:30:59,720
Come on.

566
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:36,640
Have some water.

567
00:31:36,839 --> 00:31:37,839
Here.

568
00:31:42,920 --> 00:31:43,920
Have a seat.

569
00:31:54,039 --> 00:31:55,119
I'm afraid of water.

570
00:31:59,960 --> 00:32:01,160
I can see that.

571
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:03,839
It's nothing.

572
00:32:03,839 --> 00:32:04,880
A lot of people are afraid of water.

573
00:32:05,680 --> 00:32:06,759
Some people are afraid of the water.

574
00:32:06,880 --> 00:32:08,079
Some are afraid of heights.

575
00:32:08,359 --> 00:32:09,440
Some are afraid of snakes.

576
00:32:10,640 --> 00:32:11,680
Anyway,

577
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,880
everyone has a weakness.

578
00:32:26,480 --> 00:32:27,559
My mom...

579
00:32:31,880 --> 00:32:33,920
died in the water.

580
00:32:38,480 --> 00:32:39,480
I was there with her.

581
00:32:39,480 --> 00:32:41,000
That's why I'm afraid of water...

582
00:32:42,160 --> 00:32:43,319
for an inexplicable reason.

583
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:46,960
I can't get over it.

584
00:32:56,319 --> 00:32:58,359
My mom sacrificed herself...

585
00:32:59,799 --> 00:33:01,039
to save me.

586
00:33:03,559 --> 00:33:06,759
So my mom gave me life twice.

587
00:33:10,200 --> 00:33:11,599
In danger,

588
00:33:12,680 --> 00:33:16,079
the first thing a mom always does is to save her child.

589
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:21,039
I guess it's a mother's instinct.

590
00:33:27,279 --> 00:33:28,359
I had never...

591
00:33:30,240 --> 00:33:32,000
talked about this.

592
00:33:32,119 --> 00:33:33,400
It's something I can't let go of.

593
00:33:33,400 --> 00:33:34,759
I can't resolve it.

594
00:33:35,440 --> 00:33:37,079
I wanted to talk about it,

595
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:39,200
but I just couldn't.

596
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:42,960
But I told you today.

597
00:33:44,079 --> 00:33:45,240
It turns out...

598
00:33:46,559 --> 00:33:47,720
it's not that hard.

599
00:33:54,480 --> 00:33:55,559
Every day,

600
00:33:58,759 --> 00:34:01,119
when I'm in bed late at night,

601
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:03,119
the moment I close my eyes,

602
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:08,079
the image in the water...

603
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:09,960
would show up before my eyes...

604
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:13,289
like a movie.

605
00:34:17,440 --> 00:34:19,440
It really hurts sometimes.

606
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:22,000
That's why you often can't sleep at night.

607
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:23,599
So you get up and work.

608
00:34:24,199 --> 00:34:25,199
Yes.

609
00:34:26,440 --> 00:34:29,159
I thought I might need...

610
00:34:29,159 --> 00:34:30,769
to do something else...

611
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:33,440
to distract myself.

612
00:34:33,719 --> 00:34:36,199
That's why you decided to become a rescuer.

613
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:37,960
I think...

614
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:40,880
that being a rescuer...

615
00:34:42,840 --> 00:34:44,440
is my responsibility for life.

616
00:34:47,679 --> 00:34:49,719
I feel like deep down,

617
00:34:49,719 --> 00:34:52,289
I have the desire to help people.

618
00:34:53,480 --> 00:34:54,559
I can't help it.

619
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:58,559
I hope I can be of help to everyone within my reach.

620
00:34:58,559 --> 00:35:00,000
Even though I can't do much,

621
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:03,329
I do my best and give it my all.

622
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:07,039
I wish I could save...

623
00:35:07,809 --> 00:35:09,239
every life that can be saved.

624
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:57,079
If you asked me yesterday what happiness is,

625
00:35:57,639 --> 00:35:59,960
I would say I don't know.

626
00:36:02,039 --> 00:36:05,599
If you ask me what happiness is today,

627
00:36:06,519 --> 00:36:07,719
I'll tell you...

628
00:36:09,199 --> 00:36:11,559
happiness is when your childhood dream life...

629
00:36:11,559 --> 00:36:13,039
became reality.

630
00:36:14,199 --> 00:36:16,199
I'm living my dream now.

631
00:36:17,440 --> 00:36:18,480
Thank you.

632
00:36:18,769 --> 00:36:19,960
(Moments)

633
00:37:35,559 --> 00:37:36,599
How is it, Liu Er?

634
00:37:38,639 --> 00:37:40,119
What happened?

635
00:37:40,599 --> 00:37:42,199
Did you use it as a boat?

636
00:37:43,480 --> 00:37:44,519
Don't get me started.

637
00:37:44,809 --> 00:37:46,769
I went to the mountains yesterday to buy something.

638
00:37:46,960 --> 00:37:49,289
But there was heavy rain when I came back.

639
00:37:49,289 --> 00:37:52,000
I pulled over to wait for the rain to stop.

640
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:54,199
I didn't expect my car to slip into the river.

641
00:37:54,679 --> 00:37:56,119
You didn't take the expressway again.

642
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,559
Don't you know how much it costs to travel?

643
00:37:57,559 --> 00:37:58,559
I only make so little profit.

644
00:37:58,559 --> 00:38:00,000
I don't want to spend it on the expressway.

645
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,119
Don't be silly.

646
00:38:01,119 --> 00:38:05,039
The gas money is more expensive than the expressway fees.

647
00:38:05,039 --> 00:38:07,329
Why are you everywhere? Go and sweep the floor.

648
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,079
You're not listening.

649
00:38:09,719 --> 00:38:10,719
Mr. Liu.

650
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:12,400
Mr. Liu.

651
00:38:12,559 --> 00:38:13,559
I'm good.

652
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:16,329
Please fix it.

653
00:38:16,960 --> 00:38:18,039
Is there still hope?

654
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:20,329
I'll take it back and check.

655
00:38:20,840 --> 00:38:22,079
I think...

656
00:38:22,329 --> 00:38:23,329
there is not much hope.

657
00:38:23,769 --> 00:38:25,679
Don't say that.

658
00:38:26,039 --> 00:38:27,039
Well...

659
00:38:27,329 --> 00:38:29,719
It means a lot to me.

660
00:38:29,719 --> 00:38:30,840
It's not just a car.

661
00:38:31,119 --> 00:38:32,840
